This paper is primarily focused on the detection of Android malware, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper extensively uses machine learning algorithms to detect malware, which makes it relevant to the categories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also involves the study of Android app features, which is related to software engineering (cs.SE). Finally, the paper deals with the extraction and analysis of features, which is a common task in data science (cs.DS).
